7.1.14 - M365SR14: Unmanaged Feature Updates and Lifecycle Changes
ISM controls:
•	Control: 0314; Revision: 6; Updated: Jun-21; Applicability: All; OS: All (Change management processes)
•	Control: 1560; Revision: 3; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Configuration of cloud services)
•	Control: 1506; Revision: 1; Updated: Jun-21; Applicability: All; OS: All (Evaluation of cloud service security)
________________________________________
Current Risk
Microsoft regularly add and remove features from M365 which may impact the agency in the form of introducing new vulnerabilities or impacting production services affecting the integrity, confidentiality, or availability of agency information.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
UNLIKELY	x	MAJOR	=	MEDIUM
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Establish a Cloud Change Advisory Board (CCAB): Create a dedicated cross-functional team to review the Microsoft 365 Roadmap and Message Centre updates weekly to assess impact before features are rolled out to production.
2.	Utilise Targeted Release Wings: Configure a subset of "Early Adopter" users in a targeted release ring to validate new features and identify potential security or stability issues before global deployment.
3.	Standardise Security Impact Assessments: Mandate a brief security review for any major feature changes (e.g., new collaborative apps or generative AI integrations) to ensure they align with existing governance and ISM compliance.
- Treatment #1
•	Automated Roadmap Monitoring: Use PowerShell or API integration to pull Message Centre updates into a centralised tracking system (e.g., Jira or ServiceNow) for formal architectural sign-off.
•	Governance Documentation: Maintain a "Service Definition Document" that lists all enabled M365 services and the specific risk decisions made for disabled features.
•	Continuous Configuration Auditing: Deploy automated tools like Microsoft Purview or third-party posture management (SSPM) to detect and alert on new default settings introduced by Microsoft updates.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
Proactive monitoring and a structured release process allow the agency to intercept potentially disruptive or insecure feature changes before they impact the wider environment. While the consequence of a platform change remains "Major" due to potential operational downtime, the likelihood of an unmanaged change causing a security incident is reduced to "Rare."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
RARE	x	MAJOR	=	MEDIUM

